<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> One Card combos a.k.a. epp companions<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10224'>Lucas "skitch" Heath</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10224&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 7, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> This article is a fun attempt at fixing three of the bigger problems with LOTR CCG... The first of these is the lack of cards which allow you to draw something from your draw deck, this is something Star Wars CCG was based around and it really reduces the luck aspect of the game that many complain about.  Second is that, like Star Wars, as more cards come out, it becomes harder and harder to build a deck with all the cards you want in it due to space... in Star Wars the EPP characters came of this, combining two cards that obviously fit together to save space and make the game more fun... so with this I have theorized a couple of &quot;EPP&quot; Lord of the Rings characters... this would also help with the third problem, which is for newer players to the game, it is very hard to build a deck that wins skirmishes as most of the character weapons are rare, with the exception being ranger sword, which is a pretty pricey uncommon, fetching the same price as some rares around here.  With these &quot;EPP&quot; characters, newer players could jump into the game and build decks that win skirmishes and possibly do some other things as well.  I think they would be fun as hell to play with as well.  Of course there have to be some draw backs, so each &quot;EPP&quot; character would not have a signet, and would have some sort of other drawback to it, however small.  <br />
<br />
I got the idea for these from John Arendt&#39;s deck he posted a while back, a very good deck, but he had EPP Gimli as a joke, I guess I took it a little more seriously... so here&#39;s my &quot;EPP&quot; characters... Hobbits not included (They aren&#39;t really fighters anyways).<br />
<br />
Aragorn w/ Anduril<br />
Strider<br />
Twi 5<br />
Str 10<br />
Vit 4<br />
Defender +1<br />
Response: Exert Aragorn and spot less than 4 burdens to prevent a wound to any Arwen, Frodo, Gimli or Legolas with the Aragorn signet.<br />
<br />
This might be a little too powerful, but this guy should be very powerful.  He can&#39;t exert to take on 4 minions at a time, can&#39;t heal someone every turn, and he can&#39;t be a staple in every choke deck, but he can be a protector of sorts, much as he is in the books and movie.<br />
<br />
Arwen w/ Gwemegil<br />
Twi 3<br />
Str 8<br />
Vit 3<br />
Skirmish: Discard 3 cards from hand to make Arwen strength +1 (+3 if skirmishing a Nazgul)<br />
<br />
Most closely resembles Daughter of Elrond, except it is 3 cards to pump her, the +3 is to make up for her natural strength against nazgul.  it would be pretty hard to boost her twice against those nazgul though, making her a weaker companion against nazgul than using both cards seperately.<br />
<br />
Boromir w/ Blade of Gondor<br />
Twi 4<br />
Str 9<br />
Vit 3<br />
Maneuver: Exert Boromir to take Banner of the White Tree into hand from reserve deck, reshuffle.<br />
<br />
This would completely reenact the end scene of the movie where Boromir takes on a swarm of Uruk-hai to protect the hobbits.  This combo would take both cards though, and the ability to wound Uruk-hai and Orcs by exerting would be taken away.<br />
<br />
Gimli w/Battle Axe & Hand Axe<br />
Twi 4<br />
Str 9<br />
Vit 3<br />
Maneuver: Exert Gimli to take Flurry of Blows into hand from reserve deck, reshuffle.<br />
<br />
Yet another card that helps you get a card you want out of your reserve deck.  A great addition to any dwarf deck.  His special ability can only be used 4 times and requires an exertion, but FoB is the best Dwarf pump card there is.  Maybe with this Dwarf decks would actually be popular.<br />
<br />
Gandalf w/ Staff<br />
Twi 6<br />
Str 8<br />
Vit 5<br />
Fellowship: Exert Gandalf to take any [gandalf] spell into hand from your discard pile. The Twilight cost of each [Gandalf] spell is -1.  Trust Me As You Once did may not be played.<br />
<br />
This Gandalf would be your &quot;wizard&quot; gandalf.  A must for any SotSF deck, condition removal deck, and even a Strength of Spirit deck, but at a cost... TMAYOD with this card would just be too good.  This Gandalf is more a combination of Gandalf and Barliman Butterbur, maybe a little powerful, but like Aragorn, he should be...<br />
<br />
Gandalf w/ Glamdring<br />
Twi 5<br />
Str 9<br />
Vit 4<br />
Your other companions are each strength +1.  If Gandalf Dies, your companions are each strength -1 until your next regroup phase.  Trust Me As You Once Did may not be played.<br />
<br />
This is your fighting Gandalf but once again you should not be able to play TMAYOD with him, as that would probably be too powerful.  This card reflects Gandalf&#39;s impact on the party as a leader.  His presence and lack of should have great effects on the fellowship.<br />
<br />
Legolas w/ Bow of Galadrhim & Long Knives<br />
Twi 4<br />
Str 8<br />
Vit 3<br />
Archer<br />
Each Orc or Uruk-hai skirmishing Legolas is strength -2.  Legolas may not bear [Elven] tales.<br />
Archery: Spot Legolas at a River or Forest to add 1 to the minion archery total.<br />
<br />
My favourite, Legolas with his bow and knives replaces 3 cards, and does the same thing as Son of Thranduil w/ Toys, but most notably, he cannot bear Elven Tales... no Tale of Gil-galad, no Splendor, and most notably, no White Arrows.  He is strictly a fighter, as he should be, and a good one at that.<br />
<br />
Well, I realize this article has no strategic merit... but I think these kind of cards would make the game that much cooler.  And if you think having no signet is a big draw back, I beg to differ.  I think signet is one of the most important aspects of a character...<br />
<br />
I don&#39;t know how decipher would release these, probably how they have in the past, as extras in Enhanced packs of Beta Boosters for Fellowship, or as premiums in Two Towers Starters, who knows... but it would be gosh darnit cool.<br />
<br />
My friend got into the game about two months ago, and he is not one for spending a lot of money... the hardest thing for him was getting all the weapons, at least the uncommon companions are good, and the premium Aragorn and Gandalf (Moria) are great, but without weapons, they are as good as road blocks to most Uruk-hai.<br />
<br />
Anyways... just some thoughts, thanks for wasting 5 minutes of your time to read, and thanks for your reviews and your thoughts on the cards. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=3937&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
